00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:49.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Uh...

287
00:18:49.128 --> 00:18:51.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both gasping]

288
00:18:53.174 --> 00:18:56.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, hey, folks. Sorry to interrupt.
[chuckles nervously]

289
00:18:59.263 --> 00:19:02.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] The time for your
judgment has arrived.

290
00:19:03.351 --> 00:19:04.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

291
00:19:09.273 --> 00:19:12.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you didn't really think you'd escape
from a hero of justice, did you?

292
00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Benoit] Aha!

293
00:19:22.870 --> 00:19:25.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

294
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:31.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, buddy. You're gonna have
to do better than that. Huh?

295
00:19:32.546 --> 00:19:33.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

296
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:40.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you know?
Looks like I'm doing better already, eh?

297
00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[electricity crackles]
-[screams]

298
00:19:44.308 --> 00:19:47.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[cackles] Pathetic!
Don't they have any standards?

299
00:19:47.937 --> 00:19:51.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How did a weakling like you
become a hero of justice?

300
00:19:51.649 --> 00:19:52.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

301
00:19:53.234 --> 00:19:55.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Benoit]
You ought to quit the hero business.

302
00:19:55.945 --> 00:19:57.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can't even stop a normal human!

303
00:20:00.825 --> 00:20:03.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[announcer on TV] <i>Barnaby</i>
<i>has successfully arrested the terrorists,</i>

304
00:20:03.536 --> 00:20:05.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and has rescued countless civilians!</i>

305
00:20:06.956 --> 00:20:10.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>We heroes fight for justice</i>
<i>and the hardworking people of Sternbild.</i>

306
00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:13.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[cheering]
-[thud]

307
00:20:19.051 --> 00:20:21.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cheering continues]

308
00:20:21.554 --> 00:20:23.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Barnaby! Yeah!

309
00:20:24.473 --> 00:20:26.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[club music playing]

310
00:20:27.476 --> 00:20:30.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Benoit] So... How would you like
a little spanking?

311
00:20:30.479 --> 00:20:33.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sounds like fun.
Do I look like I've been bad?

312
00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:35.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckling]

313
00:20:35.443 --> 00:20:38.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dancers gasping]

314
00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:40.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[all screaming]
-[dancer] Fire!

315
00:20:44.827 --> 00:20:46.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What the hell is that?

316
00:20:51.333 --> 00:20:54.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic] Repent, sinner.
Your judgment is at hand.

317
00:20:55.087 --> 00:20:59.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You one of those heroes, too? All right,
already! I surrender! You happy?

318
00:21:00.676 --> 00:21:03.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just kidding! [grunts]

319
00:21:04.889 --> 00:21:08.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[nervously] Sorry about that!
Guess my hand must have slipped!

320
00:21:08.309 --> 00:21:12.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The voice of Thanatos shall release you
from your dark curse.

321
00:21:13.147 --> 00:21:16.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And send you down the path
of atonement and rebirth.

322
00:21:16.984 --> 00:21:20.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[groans] Well, I guess the jig is up.
I know when I'm beat.

323
00:21:21.113 --> 00:21:24.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All right, pal, I'll come along quietly,
you happy?

324
00:21:26.702 --> 00:21:28.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you, deaf? I said I surrender.

325
00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:31.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you out of your mind?!

326
00:21:31.582 --> 00:21:34.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This isn't what heroes of justice are
supposed to do!

327
00:21:34.502 --> 00:21:40.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You made two mistakes, unfortunately.
First, I'm not a hero.

328
00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:41.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whimpers]

329
00:21:41.509 --> 00:21:45.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lunatic]
And second, this is my idea of justice.

330
00:21:51.936 --> 00:21:54.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[theme music]

